title: Personal Website!
description: What you're looking at right now! This has been apart of the DSC 106 Course at UC San Diego, but I plan to keep working on it beyond this course and hopefully set up a domain after the course is over!

title: Hydrophobic
description: My friends and I worked on a game for GMTK Game Jam, we unfortunatly couldn't compleate it, however we are still proud of what we did accomplish within 48 hours. I hope that oneday we can put up a little play ground for people to at least we what we were cooking!

title: D&D Roll Distributions
description: Created some simple python code to create dnd roll distributions with the plotly graph library. Next step, create an interactive webpage!

title: Meal Generator
description: A python script that Generates a week of meals based on a JSON files with recipes, and then creates a grocery list based on those meals for that week!

title: Pantry Pal
description: Developed an app using ChatGPT, Whisper, and DALL-E APIs, creating recipes from voice input into the app and storing account data via a MongoDB database. Course Project for CSE 110: Software Engineering at UC San Diego.

title: Choice Forest
description: For my final project in my Creative Writing class in my senior year of high school. I created a choose your own adventure story and used my new knowledge of Java to write an in compiler way of making each choice. I had only knew programming from my APCS class and I wanted to try to make something cool with that knowledge. Maybe one day I'll upgrade it to a more user friendly webpage!
